{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c17a74ae-fc6d-4f2c-9e14-eb81383a2ae3","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues in this project:\n\n---\n\n**1. Expensive Property Function — File I/O during evaluation (line 13)**\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\n`ReadAllText` executes during *evaluation*, not build. This blocks the evaluator with disk I/O. Prefer reading files via a target at build time, or use a `ReadLinesFromFile` task.\n\n**2. Overly broad wildcard glob (line 9)**\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n`**\\*.*` forces MSBuild to enumerate the entire directory tree during evaluation. This scales poorly as the repo grows. Scope the glob to specific extensions or directories.\n\n**3. Deep import chain (line 6)**\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nThree levels of chained imports. Each import is an additional file open + parse during evaluation. While 3 levels is tolerable, this pattern compounds quickly and signals a risk of uncontrolled growth.\n\n---\n\n**Summary of Recommendations**\n\n| Issue | Impact | Fix |\n|-------|--------|-----|\n| `File::ReadAllText` in property | High — synchronous I/O blocks evaluator | Move to a build target |\n| `**\\*.*` glob | Medium–High — full tree walk | Narrow to needed file types |\n| Nested import chain | Low–Medium | Flatten or consolidate props |\n\nThe highest-impact fix is removing the `ReadAllText` property function; the second is narrowing the recursive glob.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"274ee8b4-38a0-4950-8557-5bb84b17b510","outputTokens":415,"requestId":"2840:63E52:1DD591E:2113184:69FA958F"},"id":"794a7dd8-4cc3-4bfd-98e6-35662b0029d6","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:12:58.758Z","parentId":"d641df01-c1df-4743-b988-83b529b4b985"}
